convert

protected final java.lang.Object convert(java.lang.Object record)
                                  throws RecordException
Convert DataObject, or DataObject[] into some other format.
It will call the concrete subclass convert method to do the actual conversion (the subclasses will determine the output format). This class checks that the supplied record is a DataObject[], or, if a DataObject, it will wrap it as a DataObject[] before calling the concrete convert implementation.
